Citation.sTitle: Apparent molar volumes and apparent molar heat capacities of aqueous N-acetyl-D-glucosamine at temperatures from 278.15 K to 368.15 K and of aqueous N-methylacetamide at temperatures from 278.15 K to 393.15 K at the pressure 0.35 MPa
Citation.sAbstract: We determined apparent molar volumes V/ from densities measured with a vibrating-tube densimeter at 278.15 6 (T/K) 6 368.15  and apparent molar heat capacities Cp,/ with a twin fixed-cell, differential, temperature-scanning calorimeter at 278.15 6 (T/  K) 6 363.15 for aqueous solutions of N-acetyl-D-glucosamine at m from (0.01 to 1.0) mol Ae kg 1 and at p = 0.35 MPa. We also determined  V/ at 278.15 6 (T/K) 6 368.15 and Cp,/ at 278.15 6 (T/K) 6 393.15 for aqueous solutions of N-methylacetamide at m from  (0.015 to 1.0) mol Ae kg 1 and at p = 0.35 MPa. Empirical functions of m and T for each compound were fitted to our results, which  are then compared to those for N,N-dimethylacetamide. Estimated values of DrVm(m,T) and DrCp,m(m,T) for formation of aqueous  N-acetyl-D-glucosamine from aqueous D-glucose and aqueous acetamide are calculated and discussed.
